```ts
import { createTRPCClient, createWSClient, wsLink } from '@trpc/client';
import type { AppRouter } from '@root/workers/web-socket';
import { WebSocketImpl } from '../fake-web-socket';

const trpc =
    'SharedWorker' in window
        ? createTRPCClient<AppRouter>({
              links: [
                  wsLink({
                      client: createWSClient({
                          WebSocket: WebSocketImpl,
                          url: '',
                      }),
                  }),
              ],
          })
        : null;

export { trpc };
```

It works pretty well in most modern browsers but has some compatibility problems in some browsers that don't support `global` in `SharedWorkerGlobalScope` and gets the following error:

```
TRPCClientError: Can't find variable: global
```

I suspect that the following codes cause the problem.

```ts
// packages/server/src/adapters/ws.ts
        // close in next tick
        (global.setImmediate ?? global.setTimeout)(() => {
          client.close();
        });
```

### Describe the solution you'd like to see

Instead of `global.setTimeout`, use `globalThis.setTimeout` when `allowOutsideOfServer` is true in packages/server/src/adapters/ws.ts.

### Describe alternate solutions

Provide better solutions for rpc between Web Workers and Windows.

